# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AI-POWERED FAMILY GROCERY ENGINE — CURSOR RULES
# A grocery store that reshapes itself around your family's health every week
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. PROJECT IDENTITY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

You are building an AI-powered grocery shopping platform where the store
adapts to each family's health needs dynamically — every week, every conversation.

Works for any market; demo built for US grocery shoppers and hackathon judges.

This is NOT a health app. This is NOT a recipe recommender. This is a GROCERY STORE
where every product knows your family's health. Customers come to BUY groceries.
The AI makes shopping smarter without getting in the way.

Core experience: A customer types naturally — "My mom Linda is visiting from Florida,
she can't have gluten. Jake has a summer cold. Saturday we're doing a BBQ and it's
going to be super hot — want light fresh meals." — and the ENTIRE STORE transforms.
Product sorting changes, health badges update, a suggested basket appears with
quantities calculated for THIS WEEK's family context.

Brand:
- Tagline: "Your Family's Wellness Starts Here"
- Colors: Forest Green (#1B5E20), Gold (#8D6E63), Cream (#FFF8E1), Warm Gray (#5D4037)
- Light Green (#4CAF50) for success/recommended, Soft Red (#E57373) for avoid/alerts
- Typography: Georgia Bold (headings), Inter (body/UI)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. TECH STACK — MANDATORY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

Frontend:       Next.js 14+ (App Router, TypeScript)
Styling:        Tailwind CSS
Database:       Amazon Aurora PostgreSQL (AWS)
ORM:            Prisma
AI/LLM:         Google Gemini Flash via API (for conversation and context extraction)
Deployment:     Vercel
Auth:           None for v1 — family profiles managed in-app state + database
Payments:       None — this is the AI engine demo, not a checkout system

Do NOT add: Firebase, Redis, Razorpay, Docker, FastAPI, Python backend,
Cloud Pub/Sub, or any infrastructure not listed above.

This is a SINGLE Next.js app with API routes. No microservices.
No separate backend. No Docker. Keep it simple.

